    • Method Detail

      • from

        public static HttpClient from​(ArSystem system)
                       throws javax.net.ssl.SSLException
        Creates new or gets a cached HttpClient that takes its configuration details from the given Arrowhead system.

        The returned HTTP client will use the same owned identity, trust store, security mode and local network interface as the given system, which makes it suitable for communicating with other systems within the same local cloud. However, for most intents and purposes it is preferable to use the HttpConsumer class for consuming system services, as it takes care of keeping track of IP addresses, authorization tokens and other relevant details. Such an instance can with advantage be constructed from the successful result of the ArSystem.consume() method.

        If wanting to communicate with other Arrowhead systems without creating an ArSystem instance, use the HttpClient.Builder instead.

        Parameters:
        system - Arrowhead system from which to extract configuration.
        Returns:
        Created or cached client.
        Throws:
        javax.net.ssl.SSLException - If creating SSL/TLS context from given Arrowhead system fails.

      • http

        public static HttpClient http()
        Creates new or gets a cached HttpClient with a default configuration making it suitable for communicating with regular HTTP servers without encryption.

        The returned client is intended primarily for communicating with legacy systems that are known to be trusted and where encryption is infeasible to add. Its use is not advised for most kinds of production scenarios. If wanting to communicate with other Arrowhead systems, please prefer use of the from(ArSystem) method for creating HTTP clients.

        Returns:
        New or cached HTTP client.

      • https

        public static HttpClient https()
                        throws javax.net.ssl.SSLException
        Creates new or gets a cached HttpClient with a default configuration making it suitable for communicating with regular HTTPS servers.

        The client will rely on the default trust manager that comes with the system Java installation, if any, which tends to be useful for interacting with just about any Internet HTTPS server.

        The returned client is intended primarily for communicating with legacy systems and/or traditional HTTPS servers. If wanting to communicate with other Arrowhead systems, please prefer use of the from(ArSystem) method for creating HTTP clients.

        Returns:
        New or cached HTTPS client.
        Throws:
        javax.net.ssl.SSLException
